description.narrative:
The Project is expected to have high economic and developmental impact, as it will: 

- Provide a valuable positive signal to international lenders and investors as Pakistan plans to build ~10,000 MW of capacity between 2010 and 2015, most of which developed on an IPP basis; 

- Provide a much needed capacity as the installed capacity in Pakistan fails to keep up with the rapid growth of peak demand (~7% p.a.), as a result, economic actors are expressing concerns over supply deficit and load shedding measures, which are likely to continue for some time; 

- Contribute to reduce greenhouse gas emissions; 

- Create a sustained economic activity by providing job opportunities and an adequate road infrastructure thus improving life conditions of neighboring rural populations; 

- Reduce the fuel oil import burden by using a domestic source of energy which is a relief for the country's balance of trade.
